SIMPLE: footboard
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Footboard
<hw>Foot"board`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
board or narrow platfrom upon which one may stand or brace his
feet</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The platform for the engineer and
fireman of a locomotive.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The foot-rest of a
coachman's box.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A board forming the foot of a bedstead.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A treadle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Footboy</ent>⟦br⟧
